  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal, by reason of excessive vertical stacking of incompatible room types in each flat, a lack of privacy and security to the front ground floor windows caused by omission of defensible space and insufficient information to assess internal floor to ceiling height, would create a poor standard of living accommodation for future occupiers of the flats, to the detriment of their residential amenity, and would fail to be informed by Secured by Design Principles. As such, the development is contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policies D3.D(7), D6 of The London Plan (2021), Policy CS1 of the Harrow Core Strategy (2013), policies DM1, DM23 and DM26 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013), the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide Supplementary Planning Document (2010) and the Technical Housing Standards - Nationally Described Space Standards (2016).",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed alterations to the front elevation to create an extra doorway to the rear garden, and the cumulative visual impact when seen with the two main entrances, would create a cluttered and visually discordant appearance on the host building which is out of character with the pattern of development in the wider area and the streetscene contrary to the high quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policies D3.D(1) and D3.D(11) of The London Plan (2021), policy CS1.B of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), policy DM1 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010)."
  ],
